Schneider Electric Statement of Work  
 
SOW Name: Integrations Consultancy   
Supplier: Vendor A Limited, India  
Start Date: 01 September 2020 
Schneider Digital Practice: E.IT (Enterprise Applications and Architecture) 
 
CONTRACTUAL REFERENCE 
This Statement of Work (SOW) between Schneider Electric USA, Inc. , an affiliated entity of Schneider Electric 
Industries SAS   (“Schneider Electric” or “SE” or “Schneider”) and Vendor A LLC , a subsidiary of Vendor A 
Limited (“Vendor A LTD” or “Vendor A” or “Supplier”) is being executed pursuant to the Master Services 
Agreement (“MSA”) between Schneider Electric Industries SAS  and Vendor A Limited  dated 15 December 
2008 (the “Agreement”), the terms of which are incorporated herein by reference.  Any terms not defined herein 
shall have the meaning set forth in the Agreement.  
Signature of this SOW by Supplier and Schneider Electric will constitute acceptance of the terms of this SOW.  Supplier 
acknowledges and agrees that the SOW cannot be modified without Schneider Electric’s prior written consent. 
Therefore, any provisions of this SOW that Supplier deletes, amends or modifies in any way, without Schneider 
Electric’s prior written consent, will be null, void and have no effect. Following execution of this SOW, changes to the 
SOW shall only be made by a mutually agreed and signed Change Order. 
 
For the avoidance of doubt, “Consultant” is defined as an employee of the Supplier who is a resource 
assigned by the Supplier to a Schneider project. 
 
SPONSORS   
 
Schneider Digital Executive Sponsor:  Mike Anderson 
Schneider Digital Project Manager/Owner:  Madhu Rajan 
 
Supplier Executive Sponsor:  Brian Hornsby 
Supplier Program Manager:  John Sainath 
 
TERM AND TERMINATION 
This SOW is effective from 1 October 2020 and is valid until 31 March 2021. Termination of this SOW will be pursuant 
to the terms for termination as defined within the Agreement.  
 
PURPOSE  
 
Background Information 
 
Vendor A has been providing consulting and development support related to the implementation of 
Mulesoft Integrations.  
  
High Level Objectives 
 
Providing SME expertise for development of several integrations to address important business needs 
around quoting, pricing, and opportunity management.

Vendor A will provide consulting resource to support the quoting, pricing, and opportunity management work 
under this SOW and will work at the direction of the Schneider Electric project manager. 
The Vendor A Supplier Lead will act as the Vendor A single point of contact and will have control and 
supervision over the day-to-day work of the Vendor A resources including handling any issue resolutions due 
to escalations. The Vendor A Supplier Lead will evaluate the work output prior to submission to Schneider 
Digital for review and acceptance. Vendor A shall not be responsible for any delays not attributable to Vendor 
A. 
 
 Out-of-Scope 
1. All activities other than the activities stated above is out of scope for this SOW.  
2. Procurement of tools and licenses. 
3. Resources not identified in the below table, including overall Project Management which will be 
led by Schneider Electric. 
4. Any explicit work effort that is not defined as either a Vendor A responsibility will be considered a 
Schneider Electric responsibility by default.

DELIVERABLE CONDITIONS  
For any Deliverables under this SOW, the following conditions apply:

6 
 
 
  All Deliverable reviews will be performed against the Specifications set out in this SOW together with any 
requirements set forth in the Agreement.   
 No Deliverables can be deemed as accepted by Schneider Electric until Schneider Electric confirms its 
acceptance in writing. 
 For Deliverables specified under this SOW, if the deliverable does not meet the Acceptance Criteria 
specified in this SOW, the effort to get the deliverable to the expected quality level is the Supplier’s 
responsibility.  
 Schneider Electric reserves the right to return for correction, within the review period, any Deliverables that 
do not meet the Specifications set forth in this Statement of Work.  
 Supplier shall fix any defects within a reasonable time period as agreed between the Parties.  
 Acceptance criteria under this SOW are listed in Schedule A unless explicitly stated otherwise in the 
Agreement. If stated differently in the Agreement, the Agreement language governing Acceptance Criteria 
will be placed in Schedule A.  
 
ASSUMPTIONS 
 
1. Supplier warrants that all supplier resources (technology-based equipment required in the execution of the 
Services) have been legally purchased technology and software licenses. Should any additional technology 
or license need to be purchased to ensure the completion of this SOW, the fee incurred by Schneider Electric 
to purchase such technology or license for Supplier’s resources shall be invoiced to the Supplier or set off 
against payment due to Supplier.   
2. Schneider Electric will provide the project management including assigning the development request to 
the Vendor A resources. 
3. Vendor A consultants will be provided the required access to Schneider Electric systems.   
4. Schneider Electric will provide access, as required, to sufficient office accommodations, facilities, Internet 
and local network connectivity. 
5. Vendor A onsite resource will be charged based on working days consisting of 8 hours per day. No 
additional charges (e.g. over time, travel allowance, weekend work) will be considered and accepted by 
Schneider Electric. Weekend / holiday work can be compensated as time off based upon mutual 
agreement with the SE scrum team. Weekend work needs must be agreed upon in advance by Schneider 
Electric and may be required for critical program deliverables. 
6. No travel is assumed during this SOW term.

 RESPONSIBILITY MATRIX 
 
The SE and Supplier Responsibilities under this SOW follow. 
SE Responsibilities :  
 
 Provide Supplier with timely access to relevant data, documentation and personnel. 
 Provide timely input on any Supplier queries and confirm the go-forward approach as required. 
 Provide timely feedback on the quality of the Services and any issues that need to be addressed. 
 
Supplier Responsibilities : 
 Establish a regular status reporting and meeting schedule. 
 Communicate with SE in a timely manner if data quality challenges or delays in obtaining information will 
impact the Supplier’s ability to execute the assessment as defined in this SOW. 
 Communicate with SE in a timely manner if fees are anticipated to exceed the upper limit of the fee estimate 
and the reasons for such. 
 Oversee the quality of the Services to ensure they are executed in accordance with the terms of this SOW. 
 Notify SE immediately, outside of the regular status reporting time agreed, should the Supplier have findings 
which it deems will impact the scope or quality of its work.

 SOW GOVERNANCE 
 
 All issues and disputes will first be worked out between the respective project leads . If a resolution can’t be 
reached between the project leads, no longer than two weeks from the initial documentation of the issue or 
dispute, the issue or dispute will be escalated to the executive sponsors  for resolution.  
 If a resolution can’t be reached at the executive sponsor level, the issue or dispute will be worked out according 
to the terms and conditions of the Agreement.  
 All issue and dispute documentation, available to Schneider Electric and the Supplier, will be stored in a 
Schneider Electric Box folder or similar Schneider Electric controlled document repository along with any 
resolutions.

“Fixed Capacity” shall mean that Supplier provides dedicated resources to Schneider Electric to perform 
Services as per Schneider Electric’s directions and instructions. Supplier shall invoice Schneider Electric in 
full for 8.75 hours per day for offshore resource and 8 hours per day for onsite resource, irrespective of the 
fact whether Schneider Electric is able to utilize the efforts or man hours of such dedicated resources in full. 
Supplier will not invoice Schneider Electric for Supplier holidays or vacation days. 
 For Time & Material not-to-exceed SOW’s, the following conditions apply: 
o Supplier will be paid up to, but not in excess of, the not-to-exceed value of this Statement of Work. 
o The total fees to be paid to Supplier cannot be increased beyond the not-to-exceed value unless the 
Parties execute a written Change Order. 
o Supplier shall be paid based on actuals incurred. 
o Each invoice will provide a detailed breakdown of the hours worked by each consultant by day over 
the specific invoice period.

Deliverable Acceptance Criteria 
 
 All reviews will be performed on the basis of work compliance with the Specifications set out in the Statement 
of Work together with any requirements set forth in the Agreement. Schneider Electric reserves the right to 
return for correction within the review period, any Deliverables on which Schneider Electric has Reservations 
compared with the Specifications set forth in this SOW. In such a case, Supplier shall fix such Reservation(s) 
within a reasonable timeframe as agreed between the Parties. If after fifteen (15) days, and written notice by 
Supplier to Schneider Electric of delivery of the Deliverable(s), no notice of rejection of such Deliverables 
identifying in reasonable detail the Reservations have been received by Supplier from Schneider Electric, 
Supplier will send  written notice to Schneider Electric. Following such notice, Schneider Electric shall have 
an additional five (5) business days to accept, modify or reject the Deliverables, or (ii) if the Deliverables have 
been used by Schneider Electric the Deliverables will be deemed accepted. In the event that an approved 
Deliverable differs from the Specifications for such Deliverable, the Specifications shall be deemed modified 
to conform with such approved Deliverable. Notwithstanding the foregoing, approval, shall be granted by 
Schneider Electric even if a Deliverable contains minor non-conformities (such as format or style non-
conformities that do not negatively impact the functionality of the Deliverable and that require only minor or 
cosmetic corrections). 
 
Classification of Deliverables.    
 DELIVERABLE ACCEPTED, shall be defined as a Deliverable conforming to the Specifications set out in this 
Statement of Work, with no more than minor and/or isolated exceptions or nonconformities. In such case 
Schneider Electric will take responsibility for any necessary corrections. 
 
 DELIVERABLE ACCEPTED WITH REWORK, shall be defined as a Deliverable essentially conforming to its 
Specifications as set out in the Statement of Work, but having a significant number of isolated exceptions, and 
is accepted pending re-editing and correction by Supplier. Supplier shall re-edit the work for the indicated 
errors (with reference to the applicable Reservations) and resubmit within fifteen (15) days or such other period 
as agreed by the Parties. Schneider Electric will rerun its acceptance checks for the classes of errors detected 
in the initial check and will reclassify the Deliverable(s) as either ACCEPTED or REJECTED in accordance 
with the process set forth within the Agreement.  
 
 DELIVERABLE REJECTED, shall be defined as a Deliverable failing to conform to the Statement of Work’s 
Specifications in ways that indicate that there are material non-conformities to the Specifications. Supplier 
shall rework the Deliverable and resubmit to Schneider Electric within fifteen (15) days, at which time 
Schneider Electric will rerun its acceptance check and reclassify the work in accordance with the process set 
forth within the Agreement.
